<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall carry out in 1977, and in the spring of each fifth year thereafter, surveys on plantations of fruit trees existing on their territory for the production of dessert apples and pears (excluding purely cooking varieties), peaches and oranges. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid teevad 1977. aastal ja seej&auml;rel iga viienda aasta kevadel vaatlusi oma territooriumil asuvate viljapuuistandike kohta, kus toodetakse laua&otilde;unu ja -pirne (v&auml;lja arvatud t&ouml;&ouml;tlus&otilde;unad ja -pirnid), virsikuid ja apelsine. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The survey provided for in paragraph 1 shall apply to all undertakings having an area planted with the species of fruit trees referred to in paragraph 1, provided that the area covers at least 1 500 square metres and that the fruit produced are entirely or mainly intended for sale. </inglise>
